_pdbx_database_remark.text   
;
SHEET
THE SHEET STRUCTURE OF THIS MOLECULE IS BIFURCATED. IN
ORDER TO REPRESENT THIS FEATURE IN THE SHEET RECORDS BELOW,
TWO SHEETS ARE DEFINED.
;
# 
_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                 1V0V 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details         
;THIS DATASET DESCRIBES AN 8 DAY SUBSTRATE SOAK USING 2MM
 DIBUTYRYLPHOSPHATIDYLCHOLINE. A PHOSPHATE IS FOUND TO BE
 COVALENTLY LINKED TO AN ACTIVE SITE HISTIDINE, SUGGESTING
 THAT THE CATALYTIC REACTION CAN PROCEED BEYOND THAT OF
 PRODUCT FORMATION, AND THAT, IN FACT THE PRODUCT CAN
 REENTER THE ACTIVE SITE TO BE FURTHER PROCESSED.
;
